---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Terms and Conditions';
const description =
  'Moving Cars Terms and Conditions of Service. Important information regarding vehicle transport, liability, cancellations, and transit times.';
const lastUpdated = '15 January 2026';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="bg-slate-50 min-h-screen py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <div
        class="bg-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100"
      >
        <header class="mb-12 border-b border-slate-100 pb-8">
          <div
            class="text-amber-600 font-bold mb-2 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm"
          >
            Legal & Compliance
          </div>
          <h1
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-4"
          >
            Terms and Conditions
          </h1>
          <p class="text-slate-500 font-medium">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-slate prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8 font-medium">
            Your use of our site is deemed to be your acceptance of these Terms
            of Use.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            1. Privacy & Anti-Abuse
          </h2>
          <p>
            In addition to our stated privacy policies, please be advised that
            visitor I.P. addresses are automatically added to all forms
            submitted from this site. An I.P. address cannot identify you
            personally; this measure is intended solely to combat abuse and
            ensure the integrity of our quoting system.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            2. Intellectual Property & Copyrights
          </h2>
          <p>
            The presentation, design, and material displayed on this site are
            the intellectual and physical property of Moving Cars and are
            protected under Australian and International Copyright Law. Content
            or graphics may not be duplicated or distributed without express
            written consent.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            3. Liability & Our Position
          </h2>
          <p>
            Moving Cars acts as an <strong>agent on your behalf</strong> to obtain
            the best possible price and service. We do not directly transport the
            vehicles ourselves.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-700">
            <li>
              <strong>Agency Model</strong>: You understand that responsibility
              for transporting your vehicle lies with the agreed carrier.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Carrier Terms</strong>: By booking, you agree to the
              specific carrier's terms and conditions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Damage Claims</strong>: If any damage occurs, the carrier
              themselves will deal with this for you as the primary service
              provider.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>"As Is" Basis</strong>: This site is presented on an "as
              is" basis without warranty concerning technical inaccuracies.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            4. Conditions of Transport
          </h2>
          <p>
            All vehicles must comply with the following strict terms to be
            eligible for transport:
          </p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Vehicle Status</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-slate-600">
                <li>• Drivable & roadworthy condition</li>
                <li>• Functioning brakes & handbrakes</li>
                <li>• Able to start/run without a jump start</li>
                <li>• Windows and roof must be intact</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Dimensions & Weight</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-slate-600">
                <li>• Minimum 150mm (6 inch) clearance</li>
                <li>• Standard height: Below 1.90m</li>
                <li>• Max weight: 3 tonnes (unless prearranged)</li>
                <li>• Dimensions taken from furthest points</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            5. Transporting Goods Inside Vehicles
          </h2>
          <div
            class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-6 my-6 rounded-r-xl"
          >
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">"Goods in Car" Policy</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-800 text-sm mb-4">
              Vehicles must be empty unless you have selected and paid for the
              ‘Goods in Car’ option.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-slate-700">
              <li>• <strong>Limit:</strong> Strictly 80kg maximum.</li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Visibility:</strong> Goods must not block windows.
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Placement:</strong> Nothing behind the driver's seat or
                front passenger seats.
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Liability:</strong> No legal liability is accepted for loss
                or damage to goods or vehicle as a result of goods being inside.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 italic">
            Note: Spare tyres, jacks, and fitted baby seats are allowed in all
            vehicles without extra charge.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            6. Transit Times & Estimates
          </h2>
          <p>
            Transit times are always an <strong>estimate</strong> and cannot be guaranteed.
            They are calculated in business days (excluding weekends/public holidays).
          </p>
          <p>
            Estimates may vary due to seasonal peaks, acts of nature, or carrier
            backlogs. We recommend that you do not plan meetings, trips, or
            holidays based on estimated delivery dates.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            7. Cancellations & Adjustments
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-4 text-slate-700">
            <li>
              <strong>Written Notice</strong>: All cancellations must be in
              writing; we do not accept cancellations via phone.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Fees</strong>: A cancellation fee of $125.00 to $225.00
              applies depending on timing.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Futile Fees</strong>: If cancelled with less than 48 hours
              notice and a carrier attempts collection, a futile fee ($150 -
              $300+) may be charged.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>In-Transit</strong>: Once a vehicle is collected/on the
              truck, the full transport costs may be withheld as space cannot be
              re-booked.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Admin Fees</strong>: Changes to confirmed bookings may
              incur an admin fee.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            8. Special Conditions
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <section>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Auctions</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">
                Vehicles from auction houses must be drivable and have no
                damage/dents. Cars marked as "write-off" require a re-quote.
              </p>
            </section>
            <section>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900">WA Quarantine</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
                Vehicles entering WA are subject to Inspection. Contaminated
                vehicles incur a minimum cleaning charge (approx $130) payable
                directly to the carrier.
              </p>
            </section>
            <section>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Depots & Storage</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
                Storage fees may apply after 2 days at a depot (typically
                $55/day). SMB Darwin/Alice Springs depots do not provide
                insurance; customers should obtain their own coverage for these
                locations.
              </p>
            </section>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">
            9. Questions or Concerns?
          </h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about these matters, please contact us
            directly via our <a
              href="/contact-moving-cars/"
              class="text-amber-600 hover:underline">contact page</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quote CTA -->
        <div
          class="bg-slate-900 text-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-2xl mt-16 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-8"
        >
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Ready to move?</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg">
              Transparent pricing. Reliable service.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/quote/"
            class="bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-400 text-slate-900 font-bold py-4 px-10 rounded-xl transition-all transform hover:scale-105 inline-block text-center whitespace-nowrap"
          >
            Get Instant Quote
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
